# State and Logic Boundaries

## Ownership

- `src/appState/`: client-side app stores and state transitions
- `src/domain/`: business rules, capabilities, guards, resolvers
- `src/services/`: external integrations, API clients, analytics, notifications, native SDK wrappers
- `src/hooks/`: reusable hooks that coordinate state and services
- `src/utils/`: pure helper functions
- `supabase/functions/`: server-side logic and edge-function behavior

## Rules

- Keep business decisions in `src/domain` when possible.
- Keep service files focused on integration behavior, not screen rendering.
- Avoid duplicating domain rules inside UI files or stores.
- If logic is reused across features, pull it out of the feature folder.
- Prefer pure functions in `src/utils` for deterministic transformations.
- Define contracts clearly when app logic and Supabase functions evolve together.

## Parallel Work Guidance

- UI agents should consume contracts, not invent them ad hoc.
- Logic and backend changes should align on request and response shapes before parallel implementation.
- If a store shape changes, update dependent hooks and tests deliberately rather than relying on incidental fixes.
